al\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ijx1665702711766.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ijx1665702711766.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ijx1665702711766.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ijx1665702711766\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Modeled Field Layout\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__modeled_field_layout_316701\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Modeled Field Layout is a Development Object that defines the way data is displayed.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__p_d96425e1_d96426e1_d96427e1\">For example, the layout of the day, month, and year in a date field can be displayed in different formats, such as: Tuesday, 18 Jul-1974, 18/07/74, or 18-JUL-74 and so on.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__p_d96428e1_d96429e1_d96430e1\">Fields that reference a Modeled Field Layout, inherit the complete field layout definition. It the Modeled Field Layout changes, the change is applied to the fields when the component is recompiled.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__p_d96431e1_d96432e1_d96433e1\">Modeled Field Layout objects are used during development. They are linked into the component (resolved) during compilation.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__topic_d64482e1_d64483e1_d64484e1_d64485e1_d64486e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d828967e62\">\n                     \n Characteristics\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fla</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ulo1665702550460.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html\" title=\"A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\">Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ijx1665702711766__table_d10718e1_d10719e1_d10720e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">fla:<var class=\"keyword varname\">LayoutName</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__topic_d64487e1_d64488e1_d64489e1_d64490e1_d64491e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d828967e240\">\n                     \n Specialization\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__p_d96440e1_d96441e1_d96442e1\">Modeled Field Layout specializes Development Object in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__li_d39137e1_d39138e1_d39139e1\">It specifies a value for a <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Layout</span> property. This is a property of fields that determines how the data is displayed.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__li_d39140e1_d39141e1_d39142e1\">It has a Modeled Field Layout Library called\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">LIB</code> as parent object. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__li_d39143e1_d39144e1_d39145e1\">It contains no child development objects or code\n               containers. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__li_d39146e1_d39147e1_d39148e1\">It has no compiled or generated output. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__topic_d64492e1_d64493e1_d64494e1_d64495e1_d64496e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d828967e270\"> Properties </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ijx1665702711766__p_d96446e1_d96447e1_d96448e1\">Layout properties are represented by field layout\n            codes. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"iha1665702711837.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iha1665702711837.html\" title=\"Field layout codes specify how data is formatted for display. When multiple codes are specified, they must be separated by commas.\">Field Layout Codes</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613713\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3613713\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Modeled Field Layout Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Modeled Field Layout A Modeled Field Layout is a Development Object that defines the way data is displayed. For example, the layout of the day, month, and year in a date field can be displayed in different formats, such as: Tuesday, 18 Jul-1974, 18/07/74, or 18-JUL-74 and so on. Fields that reference a Modeled Field Layout, inherit the complete field layout definition. It the Modeled Field Layout changes, the change is applied to the fields when the component is recompiled. Modeled Field Layout objects are used during development. They are linked into the component (resolved) during compilation. Characteristics Characteristics Object type code: fla Main Development Object? No Part of: — Contains: Property Generalization: Development Object Specializations: — Compilation Output: — URI format: fla: LayoutName Specialization Modeled Field Layout specializes Development Object in the following ways: It specifies a value for a Field Layout property. This is a property of fields that determines how the data is displayed. It has a Modeled Field Layout Library called LIB as parent object. It contains no child development objects or code containers. It has no compiled or generated output. Properties Layout properties are represented by field layout codes. For more information, see Field Layout Codes . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}